"title": "7709: apostles, authority of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7709",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Apostolic authority derives directly from Jesus Christ, who commissions apostles. It is rigorously upheld within the church.</p>\n<h2>Apostolic authority is based on divine commission</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:5\">ROM 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:1\">2CO 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:1\">GAL 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:1\">EPH 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:1\">COL 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:1\">1TI 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:1\">2TI 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>Apostolic authority derives from Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:40\">MAT 10:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:18–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7\">MRK 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:2\">2PE 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>The authority of apostles is related to their ministry role</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a></strong> <em>There appears to be a definite order of priority with apostles at the head.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>The exercise of apostolic authority within the church</h2>\n<h3>In building up the body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:10\">2CO 13:10</a></strong> <em>Paul had special authority as founder of this church.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:8\">2CO 10:8</a></p>\n<h3>In general oversight</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:34-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:34–4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:2–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:6\">ACT 15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:23\">ACT 15:22–15:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:4\">ACT 16:4</a></p>\n<h3>In teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:2\">1TH 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:11-Gal1:12\">GAL 1:11–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4\">1TH 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:8\">1TH 4:8</a></p>\n<h3>In appointing leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a></p>\n<h3>In church discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:4\">ACT 5:3–5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:7-Acts5:9\">ACT 5:7–5:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:3-1Cor5:5\">1CO 5:3–5:5</a></p>\n<h3>The right to be supported</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:6\">1TH 2:6</a></strong> <em>Paul did not demand such support (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:9\">1Th 2:9</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:4\">1CO 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:11-1Cor9:14\">1CO 9:11–9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:7-2Cor11:9\">2CO 11:7–11:9</a></p>\n<h2>The marks of a true apostle</h2>\n<h3>False apostles exist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:2\">1CO 9:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:4-2Cor11:5\">2CO 11:4–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:11\">2CO 12:11</a></p>\n<h3>Fruit confirms apostolic ministry</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:1-2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:1–3:3</a></p>\n<h3>Signs confirm apostolic authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:12\">2CO 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:20\">MRK 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:12\">ACT 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:19\">ROM 15:19</a></p>",
